		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4864144)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4864144">
																		&quot;Super Cool Purpose&quot;:  OK sometimes!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/isnorden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6966599); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6966599&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610223863" alt="ISNorden" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6966599)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/isnorden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6966599); return false;" >ISNorden</a></span> <span class="odate time_1610002385 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Jan 2021 06:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4864144">
									

<p>If skips were never desirable. there wouldn't be so many PoIs and GoIs trying to collect them (Church of the Broken God, Scarlet King cultists, etc.) Even the grimdark artifacts tend to give <em>some</em> advantage that people want; and the not-so-grimdark artifacts can indeed be beneficial. (Healer skips like #500 and #2295 qualify; but so do object creators like #38 and #294, even if the latter are easier to abuse.)</p>
<p>As long as human beings are fallible enough to want an advantage that Those Other Guys can't duplicate &#8212; even the best-intentioned people will look for beneficial skips. As long as non-Foundation groups have enough brains to guard The Special Good Thing with every resource they can spare &#8212; those groups will Secure, Contain, and Protect whatever-it-is on their own terms.</p>
<p>The Foundationverse is a big place, with room for multiple genres and tones side by side. People who like gritty horror, wacky comedy, or some other kind of creative fiction can <em>all</em> find skips and canons they enjoy. Grimdark fans might not include anything benevolent, harmless, or likable in their headcanon. Comedy fans might not include indestructible horrors or hopeless apocalyptic scenarios in their headcanon. As long as the Foundation still takes center stage, still relies on science and research, and still cares about keeping &quot;WTF is that?&quot; phenomena away from average people&#8230;any well-done creation has a right to exist on this wiki. Yes, some tropes are difficult to reuse creatively after the first time; but &quot;difficult&quot; doesn't mean &quot;impossible&quot;.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>&quot;Anomalous&quot; just means &quot;unusual&quot;; not all surreal strangeness HAS to be evil, deadly, or even scary.</p>

				</div>
					
					
