			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-502818">
									

<p>Well, not that they don't work — I understood them okay, as did others posting here. I just think they could work better if they were clearer. As it is, the list sounds pretty unserious and unprofessional. Not that it needs to look like a EULA or anything, but if you're setting down policies and guidelines it helps to be as clear and unambiguous as possible. There could be people out there who don't understand or take seriously this kind of language, so maybe we should keep that in mind.</p>
<p>I hope I'm not imposing here — it's just the one part of the introductory materials that really stuck out for me as problematic. Maybe it's because I frequent another site (metafilter.com) that, while jokey in site-related discussions, strives to be as clear-cut as possible when it comes to official rulesetting, to eliminate any potential misunderstandings (or excuses for misunderstanding).</p>
<p>EDIT: Sorry I can't join the chat tonight — this was my last message before hitting the sack. I'll try joining tomorrow, though.</p>

							</div>

								
